{{Education-stub}}

'''Bai''' or '''baisaheb''' is a [[Suffix (name)|suffix]] added to the name of female members of the [[Maratha]] and [[Rajput]] dynasties.e.g. Shantabai It is also used as an honorific for the elder sister amongst the Marathi-speaking people. This type of suffix is also used in several [[kshatriya]] castes and in some of the tribal castes, for example the [[Lambadi]].

